{"title_page": "NHS Nightingale Hospitals", "text_new": "{{about|the three NHS Nightingale hospitals under construction by NHS England|the national field hospital network|NHS COVID-19 critical care hospitals|other hospitals|Nightingale Hospital (disambiguation)}}\n<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=NHS Nightingale Hospitals|timestamp=20200331095951|year=2020|month=March|day=31|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=NHS Nightingale Hospitals|date=31 March 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n</noinclude>{{short description|Network of temporary COVID-19 field hospitals set up by NHS England}}\n{{Merge to|NHS Nightingale Hospital|discuss=Talk:NHS Nightingale Hospital#Proposed merge of NHS Nightingale Hospitals into NHS Nightingale Hospital|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Location map many\n| United Kingdom\n| width       = \n| float       = \n| border      = \n| caption     = Location of NHS Nightingale Hospitals\n| alt         = \n| relief      = \n| AlternativeMap = \n<!--first label/marker-->\n| label1      =  London\n| label1_size =  <!-- or: label_size -->\n| position1   =  <!-- or: position, pos1, pos -->\n| background1 =  <!-- or: background, bg1, bg -->\n| mark1       =  <!-- or: mark -->\n| mark1size   =  <!-- or: marksize -->\n| link1       =  <!-- or: link -->\n| coordinates1=  {{coord|51.5081|0.0289}}\n<!--second label/marker-->\n| label2      = Birmingham\n| label2_size = \n| label2_width=\n| position2   =  <!-- or: pos2 -->\n| background2 =  <!-- or: bg2 -->\n| mark2       = \n| mark2size   = \n| link2       = \n| coordinates2= {{coord|52|27|12|N|1|43|10|W}}\n<!--third label/marker-->\n| label3      = Manchester\n| label3_size = \n| label3_width=\n| position3   =  left <!-- or: pos3 -->\n| background3 =  <!-- or: bg3 -->\n| mark3       = \n| mark3size   = \n| link3       = \n| coordinates3= {{Coord|53.476132|-2.247369}}\n<!--fourth label/marker-->\n| label4_size = \n| label4_width=\n| position4   = top <!-- or: pos4 -->\n| background4 =  <!-- or: bg4 -->\n| mark4       = \n| mark4size   = \n| link4       = \n| coordinates4= \n<!--Fifty label/marker-->\n| label5      = Bristol\n| label5_size = \n| label5_width=\n| position5   = top <!-- or: pos2 -->\n| background5 =  <!-- or: bg2 -->\n| mark5       = \n| mark5size   = \n| link5       = \n| coordinates5= {{coord|51|27|N|2|35|W}}\n<!--sixth label/marker-->\n| label6      = Harrogate\n| label6_size = \n| label6_width=\n| position6   = top <!-- or: pos2 -->\n| background6 =  <!-- or: bg2 -->\n| mark6       = \n| mark6size   = \n| link6       = \n| coordinates6= {{Coord|53.9914093677|-1.538164514}}\n<!--repeat as needed-->\n}}\nThe '''NHS Nightingale Hospitals''' are [[intensive care medicine|critical care]] [[field hospital]]s, being set up or scheduled for set up by [[National Health Service (England)|NHS England]] as part of the response to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in England|COVID-19 epidemic in England]]. The first of these hospitals to open was the [[NHS Nightingale Hospital London]].\n\n== Background ==\nAs the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in England|COVID-19 epidemic]] was spreading in England, the UK government and [[National Health Service (England)|NHS England]] were planning temporary large-scale critical care hospitals to provide cover for the projected increase in patients likely to need this type of facility.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.itv.com/news/2020-03-27/birmingham-nec-and-manchester-central-convention-complex-to-be-converted-into-coronavirus-hospitals/ |title=Two more UK facilities to be converted into 'NHS Nightingale' coronavirus hospitals |date=27 March 2020 |work=ITV News |url-status=live}}</ref> Other [[home nations]] are [[NHS COVID-19 critical care hospitals|planning similar facilities]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/in-pictures-52092253 |title=In pictures: NHS Nightingale Hospital London |date=31 March 2020 |work=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2020/03/look-inside-london-nightingale-temporary-hospitals-coronavirus/ |title=Take a look inside NHS Nightingale, London's new coronavirus hospital |website=World Economic Forum |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nOn 24 March 2020, the [[Secretary of State for Health and Social Care|UK Secretary of State for Health and Social Care]] [[Matt Hancock]], who is responsible for the NHS in England, announced that [[ExCeL London]] would be the first field hospital. It was planned to initially have 500 beds, with the capacity for 4,000 beds across its two wards if necessary later.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-up-to-10-uk-sites-could-become-makeshift-hospitals-11963733 |title=Coronavirus: Around 10 more UK sites could become makeshift hospitals |last=Haynes |first=Deborah |last2=McCann |first2=Kate |date=26 March 2020 |work=Sky News}}</ref>\n \nOn 27 March 2020, [[chief executive officer|chief executive]] of [[NHS England]] [[Simon Stevens (healthcare manager)|Sir Simon Stevens]] announced that two more temporary hospitals would open in mid-April. The identified sites are a 5,000 capacity facility at [[Birmingham|Birmingham's]] [[National Exhibition Centre]] and a further 1,000 bed provision at [[Manchester Central Convention Complex]].<ref name=BBC-uk-england-52070611>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-52070611 |title=Coronavirus: Birmingham and Manchester temporary hospitals announced |date=27 March 2020 |work=BBC News}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April 2020, the BBC reported two more NHS Nightingale hospitals were being planned - one in [[Harrogate|Harrogate, Yorkshire]] and another in Bristol. [[Simon Stevens (healthcare manager)|Simon Stevens]], head of NHS England, said the go-ahead had been given for a 500-bed facility in the [[Harrogate Convention Centre]] and a hospital of 1000 beds in the [[University of the West of England]].<ref name=\"bbc_52141224\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-52141224 |title=Coronavirus: Bristol and Harrogate Nightingale hospitals announced |date=3 April 2020 |work=BBC News}}</ref>\n\n== Staffing ==\nNursing leaders have expressed concern about where the extra workers to staff the new hospitals would be found.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nursingtimes.net/news/coronavirus/nurse-leaders-in-the-dark-about-nhs-nightingale-workforce-27-03-2020/ |title=Nurse leaders in the dark about NHS Nightingale workforce |last=Gilroy |first=Rebecca |date=27 March 2020 |website=Nursing Times |access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> The government has issued a call for airline cabin crew to volunteer to be cross-trained as specialist health assistants.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sample |first=Ian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/30/cabin-crews-drafted-help-new-coronavirus-hospitals |title=Cabin crews drafted in to help at new coronavirus hospitals |date=29 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |last2=Marsh|first2=Sarah}}</ref>\n\n==Hospitals==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+List of NHS Nightingale Hospitals\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Hospital\n! scope=\"col\" | Site location\n! scope=\"col\" | Current capacity (potential)\n! scope=\"col\" | Announced\n! scope=\"col\" | Opened (planned)\n! scope=\"col \"class=\"unsortable\" |{{abbr|Ref|References}}\n|-\n|nowrap| [[NHS Nightingale Hospital London]]\n| [[ExCeL London]]\n| 500 (4,000)\n| 24 March 2020\n| 3 April 2020\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"BBC-uk-england-52070611\" />\n|-\n|nowrap| NHS Nightingale Hospital [Birmingham]\n| [[National Exhibition Centre]], Birmingham\n| (5,000)\n|nowrap| 27 March 2020\n| \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"BBC-uk-england-52070611\" />\n|-\n|nowrap| NHS Nightingale Hospital [Manchester]\n| [[Manchester Central Convention Complex]]\n| (1,000)\n|nowrap| 27 March 2020\n| \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"BBC-uk-england-52070611\" />\n|-\n|nowrap| NHS Nightingale Hospital [Harrogate]\n| [[Harrogate Convention Centre]]\n| (500)\n|nowrap| 3 April 2020\n| \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"bbc_52141224\" />\n|-\n|nowrap| NHS Nightingale Hospital [Bristol]\n| [[University of the West of England, Bristol]]\n| (1,000)\n|nowrap| 3 April 2020\n| \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"bbc_52141224\" /><ref name=\"nbt_20200403\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nbt.nhs.uk/news-media/latest-news/nhs-nightingale-hospital-bristol |title=NHS Nightingale Hospital Bristol |website=North Bristol NHS Trust |accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"nhse_20200403\">{{cite web |url=https://www.england.nhs.uk/2020/04/nhs-to-build-more-nightingale-hospitals-as-london-set-for-opening/ |title=NHS To Build More Nightingale Hospitals, As London Set For Opening |access-date=3 April 2020 |website=NHS England}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in England]]\n[[Category:NHS COVID-19 critical care hospitals|Nightingale Hospitals]]\n[[Category:2020 establishments in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the three NHS Nightingale hospitals under construction by NHS England|the national field hospital network|NHS COVID-19 critical care hospitals|other hospitals|Nightingale Hospital (disambiguation)}}\n<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=NHS Nightingale Hospitals|timestamp=20200331095951|year=2020|month=March|day=31|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=NHS Nightingale Hospitals|date=31 March 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n</noinclude>{{short description|Netw