tion of music videos produced as a single project, or an amalgam of both); and the subsection titles 'Music video compilations' for audio-visual releases that were compiled from video music singles for later release.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | Year\n! Song title\n! Song version\n! Album title\n! Director(s)<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">''[[Best of Bowie]]'' (2002). Notes from DVD booklet. [[EMI]] (490 1030).</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1972\n| \"'''[[John, I'm Only Dancing]]'''\" [unbroadcast] {{ref label|video_singles_b|b|}}\n| original single {{ref label|video_singles_a|a|}}\n| non-album track\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Mick Rock]]<ref name=\"Pegg, p. 143\">Pegg, p. 143</ref><ref>Pegg, p. 140</ref><ref>Pegg, p. 258</ref><ref>Pegg, p. 163</ref>\n|-\n| \"'''[[The Jean Genie]]'''\"\n| single mix\n| remixed for ''Aladdin Sane'' (1973)\n|-\n| \"'''[[Space Oddity]]'''\"<br/><small>[official retrospective release (USA)]</small> {{ref label|video_singles_c|c|}}\n| version 2 {{ref label|video_singles_d|d|}} /<br/>album version {{ref label|video_singles_e|e|}}\n| ''David Bowie'' (1969) aka ''Space Oddity''\n|-\n| 1973\n| \"[[Life on Mars (song)|'''Life on Mars?''']]\"<br/><small>[official retrospective release (UK)]</small> {{ref label|video_singles_f|f|}}\n| album version\n| ''Hunky Dory'' (1971)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1977\n| \"'''[[Be My Wife]]'''\"\n| single / album version\n| ''Low'' (1977)\n| [[Stanley Dorfman]]<ref>Pegg, p. 34</ref>\n|-\n| \"[[\"Heroes\" (David Bowie song)|'''{{-'}}Heroes{{'-}}''']]\" [broadcast version]<br/>\"'''{{-'}}Heroes{{'-}}'''\" ['take 1' version] {{ref label|video_singles_g|g|}}\n| UK 7\" edit\n| ''\"Heroes\"'' (1977)\n| [[Nicholas Ferguson|Nick Ferguson]]<ref>Pegg, p. 111</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1979\n| \"[[Boys Keep Swinging]]\"\n|\n|\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[David Mallet (director)|David Mallet]]\n|-\n| \"[[DJ (David Bowie song)|DJ]]\"\n|\n|\n|-\n| \"[[Look Back in Anger]]\"\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1980\n| \"[[Ashes t