ious Moonlight]]'''''\n| 1983\n| 1984\n|\n* 12 September 1983\n* Vancouver\n* [[Serious Moonlight Tour]]\n| \n* Released: February 1984\n* Distributors: [[Warner Music Group|WarnerVision]], Pioneer Artists, [[Nikkatsu]]\n* Format: VHS, [[laserdisc|LD]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 10<br /><ref>\"[https://www.google.com/books?id=8SMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT11&dq=%22serious+moonlight%22&lr=&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=16#v=onepage&q=%22serious%20moonlight%22&f=false Top Music Videocassettes]\". ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' '''97''' (15): p. 25. 13 April 1985. Retrieved on 17 February 2010.</ref>\n|\n|-\n|'''''[[Ziggy Stardust and the Spiders from Mars (film)|Ziggy Stardust and the Spiders from Mars: The Motion Picture]]'''''\n| 1973\n| 1984\n|\n* 3 July 1973\n* Hammersmith Odeon, London, UK\n* [[Ziggy Stardust Tour]] (Leg VII: Legs V-VII aka Aladdin Sane Tour)\n| \n* Released: August 1984\n* Distributors: [[Warner Home Video]], [[Image Entertainment]]\n* Formats: VHS, LD\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \u2014\n|\n<small>BPI: Gold (2013) <ref name=\"bpi certs\"/></small>\n|-\n|'''''[[Glass Spider]]'''''\n| 1987\n| 1988\n|\n* First two weeks of November 1987\n* Sydney Entertainment Centre in Australia\n* [[Glass Spider Tour]]\n| \n* Released: 1988\n* Distributor: [[Stenton]]\n* Formats: VHS, LD\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \u2014\n|\n|-\n|'''''[[Tin Machine Live: Oy Vey, Baby|Oy Vey, Baby \u2013 Tin Machine Live at The Docks]]'''''\n| 1991\n| 1992\n|\n* 24 October 1991\n* The Docks, Hamburg, Germany\n* [[It's My Life Tour]]\n| \n* Released: 1992\n* Distributor: [[PolyGram Video]]\n* Format: VHS\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \u2014\n|\n|-\n|'''''[[A Reality Tour (film)|A Reality Tour]]'''''\n| 2003\n| 2004\n|\n* November 22\u201323, 2003\n* Point Theatre, Dublin, Ireland\n* [[A Reality Tour]]\n| \n* Rel