w\" |''La Grande Storia Del Rock''\n|\n* Released: 1979\n* Label: Deram\n* Formats: LP\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\n*\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Profile''\n|\n* Released: 1979\n* Label: Deram\n* Formats: LP\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\n*\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:8pt;\" |\"\u2014\" denotes items which were not released in that country or failed to chart.\n|-\n| colspan=\"14\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:10pt;\" |Notes\n{{refbegin|}}\n* '''a''' {{Note|note_70comps_a}} ''The World of David Bowie'' was released as ''Disco de Ouro'' in Brazil and ''Bowie'' in Japan.<ref name=Pegg409_10>Pegg, pp. 409\u201310</ref>\n* '''a''' {{Note|note_70comps_b}} ''Images 1966\u20131967'' was released as ''David Bowie Mille-Pattes Series'' in France, ''David Bowie'' in Belgium and Argentina, ''20 Bowie Classics'' in Australia, and reissued in France as ''Collection Blanche'' in 1978.<ref name=Pegg409_10 />{{refend}}\n|}\n\n=== 1980s compilations ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:17em;\" |Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:17em;\" |Album details\n! colspan=\"8\" scope=\"col\" |Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\" |[[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" |UK\n<ref name=\"guinness3\">Roberts, David (editor) (2006) [1977]. ''[[Guinness Book of British Hit Singles & Albums|British Hit Singles & Albums]]'' (19th edition). London: [[HiT Entertainment]]. pp. 72\u201373, 560. {{ISBN|1-904994-10-5}}.</ref><ref name=\"UK charts3\">\"[http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/19138/david%20bowie/]\". officialcharts.com Retrieved on 5 January 2017.</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" |AUS\n<ref name=\"aus3\">Australian chart peaks:\n\n* Top 100 ([[Kent Music Report]]) chart peaks to 