/reviews/scarlett-johansson/9660 Anywhere I Lay My Head]\". ''[[NME]]''. [[IPC Media]]. Retrieved on 11 March 2009.</ref>\n|-\n| 2013\n|''[[Reflektor (song)|Reflektor]]''\n|[[Arcade Fire]]\n| Backing vocals (\"Reflektor\")\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>\"[http://www.nme.com/news/david-bowie/72561 David Bowie's appearance on Arcade Fire's 'Reflektor' single confirmed]\". Retrieved on 10 September 2013.</ref>\n\n|}\n\n=== Remixes and alternate versions ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Song(s)\n!Album\n!Notes\n!Ref.\n|-\n|1972\n|\"[[The Supermen]]\"\n|''[[Glastonbury Fayre]]''\n|[[The Supermen#Other releases|alternate version]]\n|\n|-\n|1982\n|\"[[Cat People (Putting Out Fire)]]\"\n|''[[Cat People (1982 film)#Soundtrack|Cat People]]''\n|re-recorded for ''[[Let's Dance (David Bowie album)|Let's Dance]]''\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|\"[[I'm Afraid of Americans]]\"\n|''[[Showgirls (soundtrack)|Showgirls]]''\n|early mix\n|\n|-\n|1996\n|\"A Small Plot of Land\"\n|''[[Basquiat (film)#Music|Basqiat]]''\n|alternate mix\n|<ref>Pegg, pp. 195\u201396</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1997\n|\"[[I'm Deranged]]\", \"I'm Deranged (Reprise)\"\n|''[[Lost Highway (soundtrack)|Lost Highway]]''\n|edited\n|\n|-\n|\"Little Wonder\"\n|''[[The Saint (soundtrack)|The Saint]]''\n|[[Danny Saber]] Dance Mix\n|\n|-\n|2000\n|\"Something in the Air\"\n|''[[American Psycho (film)#Soundtrack|American Psycho]]''\n|''[[American Psycho (film)|American Psycho]]'' Remix\n|\n|-\n|2001\n|\"Candidate\"\n|''[[Intimacy (2001 film)|Intimacy]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Various-Intimacy-Original-Soundtrack/master/46357|title=Various - Intimacy (Original Soundtrack)|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref>\n|remix\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.davidbowie.com/2001/2001/08/27/two-bowie-tracks-on-intimacy-soundtrack|title=Two Bowie Tracks On Intimacy Soundtrack|website=David Bowie|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2003\n|\"Rebel Rebel\"\n|''[[Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle#Soundtrack|Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle]]''\n|[[Rebel Rebel#Other releases|re-recorded version]]\n|\n|-\n|\"[[Bring Me the Disco King]]\"\n|''[[Underworld (2003 film)#Soundtrack|Underworld]]''\n|[[Danny Lohner]] Mix\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|\"All the Madmen (Live Intro/Original LP Version)\n|''[[Mayor of the Sunset Strip]]''\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Various-Mayor-Of-The-Sunset-Strip/release/3723449|title=Various - Mayor Of The Sunset Strip|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref>\n|-\n|2005\n|\"Fame\"\n|''Hip Hop Roots''\n|extended edit by [[Jazzy Jay]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Various-Hip-Hop-Roots/release/728908|title=Various - Hip Hop Roots|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Music videos and films==\n\nThis section gives an overview of music video singles, music video films and compilations, live music films and music documentaries. See the [[David Bowie filmography]] for Bowie's acting roles in films and TV series.\n\n===Music video singles===\nThis subsection and 'Posthumous music video singles' lists music videos that were prepared to accompany single releases. See the subsection titled 'Music video films' for projects where music videos were originally conceived as films (a single video in a wider filmic setting or collection of music videos produced as a single project, or an amalgam of both); and the subsection titles 'Music video compilations' for audio-visual releases that were compiled from video music singles for later release.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | Year\n! Song title\n! Song version\n! Album title\n! Director(s)<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">''[[Best of Bowie]]'' (2002). Notes from DVD booklet. [[EMI]] (490 1030).</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1972\n| \"'''[[John, I'm Only Dancing]]'''\" [unbroadcast] {{ref label|video_singles_b|b|}}\n| original single {{ref label|video_singles_a|a|}}\n| non-album track\n| row